SIMPLE: handle
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Handle
<hw>Han"dle</hw> <pr>(h⟦acr⟧n"d'l)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <conjf>Handled</conjf>
<pr>(-d'ld)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos> <conjf>Handling</conjf>
<pr>(-dl⟦icr⟧ng)</pr>.]</vmorph> <ety>[OE. <ets>handlen</ets>, AS.
<ets>handlian</ets>; akin to D. <ets>handelen</ets> to trade, G.
<ets>handeln</ets>. See <er>Hand</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To touch;
to feel with the hand; to use or hold with the hand.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Handle</qex> me, and see; for a spirit hath not flesh.</q>
<rj><qau>Luke xxiv. 39.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>About his altar, <qex>handling</qex> holy things.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To manage in using, as a spade or a musket; to
wield; often, to manage skillfully.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>That fellow <qex>handles</qex> his bow like a crowkeeper.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To accustom to the hand; to work upon, or take care
of, with the hands.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The hardness of the winters forces the breeders to house and
<qex>handle</qex> their colts six months every year.</q> <rj><qau>Sir W.
Temple.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>To receive and transfer; to have pass through one's
hands; hence, to buy and sell; <as>as, a merchant <ex>handles</ex> a
variety of goods, or a large stock</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <def>To deal with; to make a business of.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>They that <qex>handle</qex> the law knew me not.</q> <rj><qau>Jer.
ii. 8.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>6.</sn> <def>To treat; to use, well or ill.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>How wert thou <qex>handled</qex> being prisoner?</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>7.</sn> <def>To manage; to control; to practice skill
upon.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>You shall see how I will <qex>handle</qex> her.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>8.</sn> <def>To use or manage in writing or speaking; to treat,
as a theme, an argument, or an objection.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>We will <qex>handle</qex> what persons are apt to envy others.</q>
<rj><qau>Bacon.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>To handle without gloves</b></col>. <cd>See under
<er>Glove</er>.</cd> <mark>[Colloq.]</mark></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Handle</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Handle
<hw>Han"dle</hw> <pr>(h⟦acr⟧n"d'l)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To use
the hands.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>They have hands, but they <qex>handle</qex> not.</q> <rj><qau>Ps.
cxv. 7.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Handle</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Handle
<hw>Han"dle</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[AS. <ets>handle</ets>. See
<er>Hand</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>That part of vessels,
instruments, etc., which is held in the hand when used or moved, as the
haft of a sword, the knob of a door, the bail of a kettle,
etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That of which use is made; the instrument for
effecting a purpose; a tool.</def> <rj><au>South.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>To give a handle</b></col>, <cd>to furnish an occasion or
means.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Handleable</ent>⟦br⟧
